    "client_msg_id": "A8ACC940-31E7-4FED-84CD-B7500CF96100",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "&gt;Because the crap you're building on today, it ain't gonna last. (It won't just disintegrate one day, instead it'll gradually put out shoots and suffocate all your degrees of freedom until you're totally ossified.)\n\nThat’s a pretty bold statement, given that we’re all running on systems that have lots of components that consist of C code from the seventies… ;-)\n\nThat said, I see what you’re after. We all believe it could be much better than it is. But I wouldn’t hope for the old stuff to just break. If that was a factor, it would’ve happened by now.\n\nNow I also wonder how many of us read ribbonfarm? Is there a correlation in the form of “people who like ribbonfarm also like to fix computing”?",
