  {
    "client_msg_id": "f81e673c-f7f2-4813-be73-7dd52e5446b7",
    "type": "message",
    "text": ":joy: Disclosure: I've also written for ribbonfarm.\n\nTangent: Do y'all feel post-rationalist? I sure don't, and yet that's how ribbonfarm gets grouped in <https://medium.com/intellectual-explorers-club/memetic-tribes-and-culture-war-2-0-14705c43f6bb>\n\n---\n\nThere's a reason I didn't say \"break\", and added the caveat about what \"not lasting\" means.\n\nAs a concrete example, simple tasks like copying strings, syncing to the file system and waiting on multiple file descriptors are fundamentally broken/insecure/errorprone on C. This stuff is an ongoing cost we all pay to this day, regardless of whether we program in C.\n\nExhibit B: the accretion of ruby/gem/rvm/bundler and python/distutils/pip/virtualenv. It happens because we feel disempowered to change the foundations. And yet each level up provides only temporary relief, and creates its own issues that need escaping. Escape lies downward.",
