    "client_msg_id": "2c2118ff-1457-485f-bc62-6c15040e181c",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I'm actually using `choice` in my current language draft :slightly_smiling_face:\nI don't follow where you're going with the observation on concatenative languages. For better or worse, Mu isn't concatenative. Instructions take operands and there's no stack.\nIt's been kinda interesting to me that I keep looking at Forth as a way to build a language in very little assembly/machine code, and then keep passing and moving on. I think it's my need for at least some minimal type system.",
